	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64183869"><p>From the schematic I looked at, they shouldn't come out at all if torqued anywhere close to correctly. It's a bolt and nut assembly that locks the plug in place.  If the nut came off, the bolt would have to come out before the plug would release.  So the nut and bolt would be loose when the plug flew away and would most likely be permanently lost.  It SHOULD be a pretty vibration resistant setup.</p><p>That said, whether the bolt was actually inserted, and whether the nut was attached at all, well, that's a big qu<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64183869">

