	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64184083"><p>There's an interesting story on pprune.org that the aircraft needed some rivets and the plug's seal being replaced. So there's paperwork for the replacement of the rivets and the seal, but none for the reinstalling of the plug. Because it is in the books as a door, and closing a door doesn't require paperwork. Except this door has bolts and nuts and split pins that must be properly installed. Calling this plug a door might have punched a huge hole in several layers of the Swiss Cheese model.</p></div>
	</div>

