	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64183769">When I saw a diagram of how the plug is designed, I don't see how lock wire would have helped. It looks like the bolts are threaded in from the interior side of the plane into taps in the door plug. These are probably steel bolts and I think it's a fair chance that the taps are aluminum, and these are oriented in the same direction as the outwards force. If the taps are indeed aluminum, all this put together pretty much guarantees the bolts are going to loosen up as the steel wears down the aluminum threads</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64183769">

