	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64184203">The bolts could have sheared. Looking at their usage in the plug door, I can easily see why you might not want to use those bolts to block pin travel. If those bolts deform along their length, you will never get them back out without cutting. It's an odd design since most applications for bolts are designed to place the forces along the axis of the bolt.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64184203">

